{"questionId":"9082301","questionHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The carbon isotope <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{14}{6}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>14</mn>\n    <mn>6</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>C is radioactive. It decays according to the equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{14}{6}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>14</mn>\n    <mn>6</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>C&nbsp;→&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{14}{7}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>14</mn>\n    <mn>7</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>N + X + Y</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">What are X and Y?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c3d87d160517a1744cccb339bb9acc6f83006a0e.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9082301","referenceCode":"19M.1A.SL.TZ1.23","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"The carbon isotope 14 6 C is radioactive. It decays according to the equation 14 6 C → 14 7 N + X + Y What are X and Y?","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"23","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["E. Nuclear and quantum physics","E.3 Radioactive decay"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}